My goal with this work was to capture the dynamism and movement in a busy city. Inspired from my slow, contemplative walks around the city of London during 2021. 

Created with JavaScript, p5.js and canvas.

metadata.name: Fractal Flower #48
metadata.description:
In this series I continue my exploration of the Mandelbrot set. This iconic fractal can be tweaked and used to make many different organic looking effects. 

Rarity comes from the following modifiers:
- Star = 10%
- Web = 10%
- Guiding Star = 5%
- Shapeshifter = 5%
- Rippler = 2.5%

metadata.name: Cold Mountain #59
metadata.description:
An impressionistic painting of a maintain on a foggy winter's day. The view will be of a mountain, mountain range, valley, or meadow. At nite, the lights come on, and the trees glow in the moonlight.

The image size is 928x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot.

Common features:
- mountain size and stroke quality
- line quality of the trees
- 50/50 to have a spiral around the sun
- large palette with different application methods

Uncommon
- outline of the first mountain and sun
- amplified color/hue shifting

Rare
- nighttime
- no sun

metadata.name: Impossible landscapes #18
metadata.description:
Impossible landscapes are generative loops and animated pieces creating a landscape with a digital painting effect.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme.
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).

metadata.name: Permutation City #154
metadata.description:
The work is inspired by the novel Permutation City by Greg Egan, the author of the hard science fiction.

It raises the issue of whether we can in principle understand that we exist in reality or in a simulation.

According to the Theory of Dust (which is described in the novel), the universe is simulatable and all other possible universes are equally as real as ours, emerging spontaneously from their own mathematical self-consistency. Human consciousness is Turing-computable, which means that consciousness can be also produced by a computer program.

The Autoverse is an artificial life simulator, a massive complex cellular automaton universe, producing cities and the consciousness of human copies.

Gradually, due to failures and a lack of computing power, the idea of the reliability of such universes is destroyed. 

Spaces crumble, cities become fluid and drain down, turning into dust and digital glitch.

Thanks to Yulikolay for helping with code, using p5.Riso.js library for generating files suitable for risograph printing.
Source images for permutation cities are made with a help of DALL·E mini neural network.

metadata.name: DeStijl Fortunes #132
metadata.description:
The best part of being full and happy and ready to leave the restaurant is opening the fortune cookie. Does it mean something? Does it have poor grammar and vague references? You know it's not really *for you* but it sure feels like it.
This collab between sgt_slaughtermelon and 0xphiiil creates simple pleasant DeStijl-influenced designs determined by your hash and inspired by Theo Van Doesburg that feature crypto-centric fortunes. Maybe they'll give you some *not financial advice* or maybe it will be a vague truism or an optimistic or pessimistic omen. Who knows? Part of the fun is imagining that it's for you and it's real - and if you don't like it, just open another cookie.

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #30
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

metadata.name: Visa to the stars #109
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: Impending Cloths #25
metadata.description:
IC makes use of fabric's potential for contrasts.
The same piece of cloth can seem to be falling, perfectly still and ready to be blown away, all at the same time.
It can look "very digital" while also achieving a high degree of texture. And so on, and so forth. Contrast and potential.
Also, "h" can be pressed to download in high resolution, although it may take up to a minute.
